gomodel:SYNGO_1001  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The paper makes use of a conditionally-floxed beta-catenin CKO mouse line. The conditional deletion is achieved via a CaMKII-cre transgenic allele (this results in a deletion at around P18).\nFigure 2: electron microscopy of stratum radiatum synapses shows:\n- a 25% increase in the number of excitatory, spine synapses (2A,B,D) in the CKO.\n- a 3-fold increase in perforated synapses (2C,E) in the CKO.\n- a 40% reduction in the undocked pool of vesicles per synapse (2F) in the CKO.\n- The number of docked vesicles located less than one vesicle diameter from\nthe presynaptic membrane was similar (Figures 2A, 2B, and 2F).\n- The reduction in the number of vesicles per synapse in the CKO is not due to redistribution of vesicles over a larger number of synapses. Quantification of the total number of vesicles (in a defined region) shows a 30% reduction in the total number of vesicles.\n\nTaken together these data suggest a presynaptic role of beta-catenin in vesicle clustering at the reserve pool region adjacent to the active zone.. Experimental description: 'To generate mice lacking β-catenin in excitatory neurons in the hippocampus, mice with two loxP-flanked β-catenin alleles (β-catenin flox/flox) were crossed with mice in which CamKII regulatory elements control cre recombinase expression (CamKcre).'" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" ;
        dc:date           "2018-01-25" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1001" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

